<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Geld" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Geld,</orth> (partic. <emph>gelded,</emph> but once <cit><quote>gelt:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 5.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 144</bibl></cit>) 1) to castrate: <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.242" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 242</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.1.147" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 1, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.174" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 133</bibl>.<lb />2) to deprive of an essential part: <cit><quote>Aquitaine so --ed as it is,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 149</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ing the opposed continent,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 110</bibl></cit>. With <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>to g. a codpiece of a purse,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.623" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 623</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed of his patrimony,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.237" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 237</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>